<esp:sh>Normalized</esp:sh>

<p>For transcription (normalized text) the following character repertoire
is supported:</p>

<table class="pretty">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Literal</th><th>U+</th><th>Name</th><th>ASCII</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>abdefghijklmnpqrstuvxyz</td><td>(themselves)</td></tr>
<tr><td>ā</td><td>U+0101</td><td>LATIN SMALL LETTER A WITH MACRON</td><td>=a</td></tr>
<tr><td>ē</td><td>U+0113</td><td>LATIN SMALL LETTER E WITH MACRON</td><td>=e</td></tr>
<tr><td>ī</td><td>U+012B</td><td>LATIN SMALL LETTER I WITH MACRON</td><td>=i</td></tr>
<tr><td>ū</td><td>U+016B</td><td>LATIN SMALL LETTER U WITH MACRON</td><td>=u</td></tr>
<tr><td>ç</td><td>U+00E7</td><td>LATIN
SMALL LETTER C WITH CEDILLA</td><td>c,</td></tr>
<tr><td>č</td><td>U+010D</td><td>LATIN
SMALL LETTER S WITH CARON</td><td>c'</td></tr>
<tr><td>ṛ</td><td>U+1E5B</td><td>LATIN
SMALL LETTER R WITH DOT BELOW</td><td>r,</td></tr>
<tr><td>š</td><td>U+0161</td><td>LATIN
SMALL LETTER S WITH CARON</td><td>$</td></tr>
<tr><td>θ</td><td>U+03B8</td><td>GREEK
SMALL LETTER THETA</td><td>t'</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>All but one uppercase transcription is the simple uppercase
equivalent of the lowercase versions in the table above.  The
exception is uppercase SHIN, which in ASCII transcription may
be obtained via the percent-sign (<code>%</code>).</p>

<esp:h>Examples</esp:h>

<esp:sh>Graphemic</esp:sh>

<pre class="cookbook">
%peo b-g : v-z-r-k : a-u-r-m-z-d-a : ...h-y
$-i-y-a-t-i-m a-d-a : m-r-t-i-y-h-y-a : h-y :
x-$-a-y-r-$-a-m : x-$-a-y-t'-i-y-m : a-ku-u-n-u-$
: a-i-v-m : p-ru-u-n-a-m : x-$-a-y-t'-i-y-m
</pre>

<esp:sh>Normalized</esp:sh>

<pre class="cookbook">
%peo/n r,=a

=&gt;      ṛā
</pre>

